Detailed Description

An Impinj-specific implementation of the Gen2V2 TagAuthenticate command; for use only with Impinj M77X chips.

◆ ChallengeMessage

override TagData Impinj.OctaneSdk.TagImpinjAuthenticateOp.ChallengeMessage
getset

The user provided 48 bit clear text message to be sent to the tag to encrypt.

For ImpinjTagAuthenticate the clear text message is 42 bits, preceded by a fixed header whose 6th bit indicates if the tag should add the "short" TID in its reply.

Here we accept a 48 bit TagData, but note that we will overwrite bits 1 through 6 when generating the header.

◆ SendReply

override bool Impinj.OctaneSdk.TagImpinjAuthenticateOp.SendReply
